---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import Card from '../components/Card';
---

<MainLayout
  title="Accessibility Statement"
  description="Simple Calculators is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities. Learn about our accessibility features and standards."
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">Accessibility Statement</h1>
    
    <Card>
      <div class="prose prose-slate max-w-none">
        <p class="text-slate-600 mb-6">
          Simple Calculators is committed to ensuring digital accessibility for people with disabilities. 
          We are continually improving the user experience for everyone and applying the relevant accessibility standards.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-6 mb-3">Conformance Status</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">
          The Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) define requirements for designers and developers to improve 
          accessibility for people with disabilities. It defines three levels of conformance: Level A, Level AA, and Level AAA.
        </p>
        <p class="text-slate-600 mb-6">
          Simple Calculators is partially conformant with WCAG 2.1 level AA. Partially conformant means that some parts 
          of the content do not fully conform to the accessibility standard.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-6 mb-3">Accessibility Features</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-slate-600 space-y-2 mb-6">
          <li>Semantic HTML structure with proper heading hierarchy</li>
          <li>Landmark regions (header, nav, main, footer) for screen reader navigation</li>
          <li>Keyboard-accessible navigation and interactive elements</li>
          <li>Sufficient color contrast ratios for text readability</li>
          <li>Responsive design that works across devices and screen sizes</li>
          <li>Clear and descriptive labels for form inputs</li>
          <li>Alt text and ARIA labels where appropriate</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-6 mb-3">Known Limitations</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 mb-6">
          Despite our best efforts to ensure accessibility, there may be some limitations. We are actively working to 
          identify and resolve any accessibility barriers. If you encounter any issues, please let us know.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-6 mb-3">Feedback</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">
          We welcome your feedback on the accessibility of Simple Calculators. If you encounter accessibility barriers 
          or have suggestions for improvement, please contact us:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-slate-600 space-y-2 mb-6">
          <li>Visit our <a href="/contact" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-700 underline">contact page</a></li>
          <li>We aim to respond to accessibility feedback within 5 business days</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-6 mb-3">Technical Specifications</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4">
          Accessibility of Simple Calculators relies on the following technologies to work with the particular 
          combination of web browser and any assistive technologies or plugins installed on your computer:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 text-slate-600 space-y-2 mb-6">
          <li>HTML</li>
          <li>CSS</li>
          <li>JavaScript</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="text-slate-600 mb-6">
          These technologies are relied upon for conformance with the accessibility standards used.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 mt-6 mb-3">Assessment Approach</h2>
        <p class="text-slate-600 mb-6">
          Simple Calculators assessed the accessibility of this website through self-evaluation and ongoing testing 
          with accessibility tools and manual checks.
        </p>

        <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mt-8 pt-6 border-t border-slate-200">
          This statement was last updated on February 19, 2026.
        </p>
      </div>
    </Card>
  </div>
</MainLayout>
